ce:section.ce:para:
Biocompatibility is an important factor that determines the feasibility of nanomaterials for biological applications. To research the biomedical application potential, MTT assays were first carried out to evaluate the cytotoxicity of NCDs-Au using the HeLa cells and HT-29 cells. As shown in Fig. 5
                        , different concentrations of NCDs-Au were used to culture HeLa cells and HT-29 cells, more than 88.9% HeLa cells and 90.3% HT-29 cells were viable even after incubated with different concentration of NCDs-Au even up to 300 μg/mL for 24 h. The confocal images of HeLa cells and HT-29 cells (Fig. 6
                        ) treated with NCDs-Au displayed their good cell imaging capability in blue and red channels. According to the results of cells viability and cell imaging, we can confirm that NCDs-Au probe has low cytotoxicity and excellent biocompatibility, and can be effectively applied for bioimaging and cell tracking.
